@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

This is a small utility that is able to rename file names! Hmm, a rename
command you think, why the hell I should need that?

mrename is much more flexible than the original rename command. It can add
extension, convert filenames to lower and to upper case, rename a bunch of
files at once, select files to rename via pattern matching, act
recursively and and and... ;-)

NOTE: At the moment mrename can do all of these things, but it can´t do a
simple rename, e.g. rename one filename to a specified other filename. It
was not intended to do such a thing, as I created mrename to rename
multiple files.

However I might add such an option later on, when I know how to implement
it so that it can act on more than one file. Maybe a replace option would
be the solution.

But now enough, it is 00:18 and I want to get ready with this bloody doc
this night and then upload the whole thing to aminet ;-)

@ENDNODE

