@NODE Usage "Usage"

mrename has the following template:

FILES/A/M,ALL/S/K,TOUPPER/S,TOLOWER/S,CAPITALIZE/S,NEWEXT,ONLYFILES/S,
ONLYDIRS/S,TEST/S


FILES       Multiple filenames, pattern matching allowed.
ALL         Recursively enter each directory that matches the pattern.

TOUPPER     Convert all filenames to UPPER CASE.
TOLOWER     Convert all filenames to lower case.
CAPITALIZE  Convert all filenames so that the 1st letter is
            UPPERCASE and each letter after a " " is also UPPERCASE.

            NOTE: CAPITALIZE doesn´t change any other characters in the
            filename, so if you want that all other characerters are lower
            case then add TOLOWER to your options. This works cause
            Capitalisation will be done after lowercasing.

NEWEXT      Replace existing filename extensions with the one given with
            this option.

            Don´t give a preceding ".", just give only the extension!

ONLYFILES   Only act on files.
ONLYDIRS    Only act on directories.

            Default is that mrename acts on files and directories.

TEST        Just test what happens, now file will be actually renamed!
            I recommend using this switch if you are not sure about,
            if the filenames and other options you specified just would
            do what you want!

            Better test before you cry about what mrename has done to
            your files afterwards ;-)


Examples (the test directory is supplied with the distribution):

Do a "cd testdir" before testing this

mrename #? CAPITALIZE

Will Capitalize all files and directories in the actual directory, does
not enter sub directories.

mrename #? TOUPPER ALL ONLYFILES

Will recursively UPPERCASE all files in the actual directory and all sub
directories.

mrename #?.gif CAPITALIZE TOLOWER ONLYFILES NEWEXT jpg

Will take every #?.gif file, replace the extension with jpg, lowercase it,
and capitalize it.

NOTE: if you would have written JPG as extension, you would have still get
lowercase jpg as extension cause all recasing is done after adding the
extension.

@ENDNODE

